terms.definition: A balanced search tree where every internal node has either two or three children. All leaves are at the same depth guaranteeing O(log n) operations and forming the conceptual basis for red-black trees.
Chip packaging technique placing multiple dies side by side on a silicon interposer for high-bandwidth die-to-die communication. Used in HBM memory stacks connected to GPU dies.
A collection of approximately 20000 newsgroup documents partitioned across 20 different discussion groups. A classic benchmark for text classification and topic modeling algorithms.
A multi-hop question answering dataset constructed from Wikipedia requiring reasoning across two documents. Provides structured evidence chains for evaluating multi-hop reasoning.
Chip packaging technology stacking multiple die layers vertically with through-silicon vias for connections. Enables higher density and shorter interconnects than planar designs.
Ethernet standard providing 400 gigabits per second bandwidth. Increasingly deployed in AI data centers as a cost-effective high-bandwidth networking option for GPU cluster interconnects.
Next-generation Ethernet standard providing 800 gigabits per second bandwidth. Being developed to meet the growing bandwidth demands of large-scale AI training clusters.
